label.value: slowest frequency for MS level 1 collection

value.value: The slowest acquisition speed with which precursor MS scans were collected. Scan acquisition frequency can be used to gauge the suitability of used instrument settings for the sample content used.

label.value: slowest frequency for MS level 2 collection

value.value: The slowest acquisition speed with which product MS scans were collected. Scan acquisition frequency can be used to gauge the suitability of used instrument settings for the sample content used.
The number of times where MS1 TIC increased more than 10-fold between adjacent MS1 scans.

definition.value: An unusual high count of signal jumps or falls may indicate ESI stability issues.

value.value: The number of times where MS1 TIC decreased more than 10-fold between adjacent MS1 scans.

definition.value: An unusual high count of signal jumps or falls may indicate ESI stability issues.

value.value: Number of MS1 scans where the scans' peaks intensity sums to 0 (i.e. no peaks or only 0-intensity peaks).

definition.value: An unusual high number may indicate incomplete sampling/scan rate of the MS instrument, low sample volume and/or failed injection of a sample.

value.value: Number of MS2 scans where the scans' peaks intensity sums to 0 (i.e. no peaks or only 0-intensity peaks).

definition.value: An unusual high number may indicate incomplete sampling/scan rate of the MS instrument, low sample volume and/or failed injection of a sample.

value.value: Number of MS3 scans where the scans' peaks intensity sums to 0 (i.e. no peaks or only 0-intensity peaks).

definition.value: An unusual high number may indicate incomplete sampling/scan rate of the MS instrument, low sample volume and/or failed injection of a sample.

label.value: number of detected quantification data points

value.value: The number of data points detected for quantification purposes within the run. These data points may be for example XIC profiles, isotopic pattern areas, or reporter ions (see MS:1001805). The used type should be noted in the metadata or analysis methods section of the recording file for the respective run.

label.value: number of identified quantification data points

value.value: The number of identified data points for quantification purposes within the run after user defined acceptance criteria are applied.  These data points may be for example XIC profiles, isotopic pattern areas, or reporter ions (see MS:1001805). The used type should be noted in the metadata or analysis methods section of the recording file for the respective run. In case of multiple acceptance criteria (FDR) available in proteomics, PSM-level FDR should be used for better comparability.
Tabular representation of the total ion current detected in each of a series of mass spectra.
Tabular representation of the parameters around ion selection like the amount of time spent filling an ion trapping device for each scan acquisition.

label.value: MS1 frequency in equal parts of subsequent RT

value.value: Average MS1 frequency during retention time periods between adjacent retention time quantiles. (Four values implies values for 1st, 2nd, 3rd, 4th quarter.)

definition.value: Acquisition frequency can be used to gauge the suitability of instrument settings depending on the sample content.

label.value: MS2 frequency in equal parts of subsequent RT

value.value: Average MS2 frequency  during retention time periods between adjacent retention time quantiles. (Four values implies values for 1st, 2nd, 3rd, 4th quarter.)

definition.value: Acquisition frequency can be used to gauge the suitability of instrument settings depending on the sample content.
